1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:02,310
(Episode 101)

2
00:00:02,310 --> 00:00:03,640
It has to be here somewhere.

3
00:00:04,110 --> 00:00:07,580
I'm sure it had a four-leaf clover
embroidered on it.

4
00:00:08,010 --> 00:00:09,110
I have to make sure.

5
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,340
It's exactly the same.

6
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:35,110
Then that means...

7
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:38,210
Jung Suk Hee is Chairman Ma's daughter?

8
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:42,580
What does this mean?

9
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:46,620
Dong Seok and Suk Hee are siblings,
and they had a baby?

10
00:00:47,790 --> 00:00:49,820
No. That can't be right.

11
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:52,220
What am I even thinking?

12
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:55,860
Besides, I thought they said
Chairman Ma's daughter was dead.

13
00:01:00,230 --> 00:01:03,400
This is a family photo,
but Dong Seok isn't in it.

14
00:01:06,170 --> 00:01:09,110
Right. I was getting carried away.

15
00:01:09,710 --> 00:01:10,880
There's no way.

16
00:01:12,010 --> 00:01:13,380
How could siblings...

17
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,250
Yes, this is ridiculous.

18
00:01:21,850 --> 00:01:23,890
What are you doing in there?

19
00:01:24,790 --> 00:01:26,760
- You scared me!
- You scared me more!

20
00:01:27,090 --> 00:01:28,460
What is all this...

21
00:01:28,590 --> 00:01:31,000
This room is a mess. What's this?

22
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:32,660
Get out!

23
00:01:33,030 --> 00:01:34,670
Why are you barging
into my daughter's room?

24
00:01:34,830 --> 00:01:38,140
That's rich. How is Seo Rin your daughter?
She's Jung Suk Hee's.

25
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,510
- She's downstairs right now.
- Shut up and get out.

26
00:01:41,010 --> 00:01:42,240
I need to clean this up, so get out.

27
00:01:43,010 --> 00:01:45,680
Honestly, why does Seo Rin
have to be so messy?

28
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,250
Don't just stand there.
I told you to get out.

29
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,320
Alright, fine, I'm going.

30
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:55,650
Gosh, my husband is so fickle.

31
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:58,820
Why would he let you back in the house?

32
00:01:58,820 --> 00:01:59,960
Why you...

33
00:02:15,970 --> 00:02:19,940
If Hwa Young had seen me return this,
I'd have been in big trouble.

34
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:23,480
This thing is more trouble
than it's worth.

35
00:02:28,550 --> 00:02:30,290
Come on, let's drink this.

36
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:33,930
Mom, this is hot.
Let it cool down before you drink it.

37
00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:39,100
Okay. Thank you, Grandfather.

38
00:02:47,370 --> 00:02:50,480
What a treat.
I'm seeing Tae Pyung so often these days.

39
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:58,050
Why is this so heavy?

40
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:02,190
You brought so much.
It's so heavy, I can't even lift it.

41
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:05,290
I'll take it to the kitchen for you.

42
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:08,930
Goodness, would you, handsome?

43
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:14,530
I brought a present for you, Grandfather.

44
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:17,500
Suk Hee brought you a present.

45
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:19,240
A present?

46
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,410
You really didn't have to.

47
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,580
It's a bracelet Mom made.

48
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:26,810
She likes to give them to people
as good luck charms.

49
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,820
What? It's gone.

50
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:35,820
What? My present is gone.

51
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,220
It's gone?

52
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,730
You must have dropped it on the way here.

53
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:44,560
It's okay. Please don't worry about it.

54
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:48,470
No! I really wanted to give it
to you, Grandfather.

55
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:52,840
It's okay. We can make him another one
for next time. Right?

56
00:03:53,170 --> 00:03:54,710
What's all this about a present?

57
00:03:55,770 --> 00:03:56,910
What?

58
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:00,650
A thief! Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

59
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:01,880
Thief! Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

60
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,650
A thief? That's going too far.

61
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:08,220
Did your mom just finish
watching a soap opera?

62
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:11,460
Why is she spouting such nonsense?
It's really upsetting.

63
00:04:12,490 --> 00:04:15,890
She is a thief!
She's the thief who stole my hairpin!

64
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:19,360
Mom, remember we promised
you'd be quiet here.

65
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:24,500
Okay. I won't point at the thief.

66
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,540
I could just...

67
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:30,170
It's amazing how little
they resemble each other.

68
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,710
She can't be his daughter.

69
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:36,150
There is no way that half-wit
could ever be the Chairman's daughter.

70
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,480
- Gosh, this is amazing.
- Here.

71
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:44,190
What are you doing?

72
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:47,930
What do you mean? I just wanted
to feed you something nice.

73
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,160
Goodness.

74
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:52,930
This is very rare wild ginseng
that's usually reserved for the Chairman.

75
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:55,430
- But...
- Just chew it well and swallow.

76
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:59,100
It'll warm you right up
and give you a burst of energy.

77
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,140
It's the best thing for your stamina.

78
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:04,640
Why did you feed me
something this valuable?

79
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,910
What if the Chairman finds out?

80
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,750
Then we'll just make sure he doesn't.

81
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:12,320
Today,
you and I have our own little secret.

82
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:16,090
- You get it, right?
- Get what? What is there to get?

83
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:18,090
I should get going now.

84
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,660
Hey, you can't just eat that ginseng
and run.

85
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:23,630
Stay and have a little fun with me. Okay?

86
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:31,100
I don't know if you've heard the news,

87
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,210
but I'm thinking about having Jang Mi...

88
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:37,480
marry Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

89
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,340
What are your thoughts?

90
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:42,380
Baek Ho is good. Baek Ho is nice.

91
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:46,180
Jang Mi and Baek Ho are good.
Marriage is good.

92
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,850
Father, I'll go upstairs now.

93
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,220
Go on.

94
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:54,260
I suppose this isn't your place
to be, anyway.

95
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:03,100
Mom, Grandfather gave
Baek Ho and me his blessing to marry.

96
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:07,740
Grandfather,
when do you think would be a good time?

97
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:10,140
Please, pick a wedding date for us.

98
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:14,210
What?
The Chairman approved of the wedding?

99
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:15,950
Come on, Mom.

100
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:18,780
Look, just know that for now.
We'll talk later.

101
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,990
- Later?
- There's no need for that.

102
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:24,790
I know the Chairman gave you his blessing
to marry Jang Mi.

103
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:28,690
But that marriage will never happen.

104
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,830
What's that supposed to mean?

105
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:35,200
Weren't you the one who was going to marry
Chairman Ma's granddaughter?

106
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,340
Is there some rule that says
Baek Ho isn't allowed to?

107
00:06:38,970 --> 00:06:39,970
Yes.

108
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:43,270
The woman Baek Ho is trying to marry
is Oh Jang Mi, the woman I love.

109
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,710
Jang Mi...

110
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,550
only pretended she would marry you
to protect me.

111
00:06:47,610 --> 00:06:49,780
- Not because she's in love with you.
- Shut up.

112
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:52,320
- Stop making excuses.
- That's enough, you two.

113
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:55,390
What is wrong with you two?
Brothers fighting over the same woman?

114
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:59,190
If Jang Mi really loved you,
would she have married me?

115
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:01,030
Is marriage some kind of joke?

116
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:03,290
Getting married to a man
she doesn't even love?

117
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,730
You know it's true.

118
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:07,170
You know how much Jang Mi
and I love each other.

119
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:10,330
I've loved Jang Mi from the beginning,
and she's only ever loved me.

120
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,600
That's just your side of the story.

121
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:15,570
The fact of the matter is,
Jang Mi was going to marry me.

122
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:18,540
- No, she's marrying me now! Me!
- Enough.

123
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,750
No matter what,

124
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,980
I will never approve of
Jun Ho marrying Oh Jang Mi.

125
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,520
You want to know why?

126
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:28,950
It's because you're Chae Hwa Young's son,
Jun Ho.

127
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:32,460
- What did you just say?
- If I knew you were Chae Hwa Young's son,

128
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,760
I never would have approved that marriage.

129
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:38,830
How can my son, Jun Ho, be the son
of that witch, Chae Hwa Young?

130
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:43,030
Just thinking about it is devastating.
After everything I did to raise you.

131
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,000
Do you think I chose to be her son?

132
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:47,410
Mother, how can you do this to me, too?

133
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:50,170
Jun Ho...

134
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:51,810
Mom.

135
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,980
Mom, you're going to make yourself sick
at this rate.

136
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:57,450
My blood boils
whenever I look at your brother.

137
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:59,120
What am I going to do?

138
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,490
What's done is done,
and we can't turn back time.

139
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:05,290
It's not like he asked to be
Chae Hwa Young's son.

140
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:06,990
That's exactly my point.

141
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:11,660
That's why I'm trying even harder
to treat Jun Ho well. I really am.

142
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:12,700
But honestly,

143
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,770
I just don't know if trying is enough
for something like this.

144
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,540
Stop it!
What did Jun Ho do to deserve this?

145
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:23,210
Is it such a mortal sin
for him to be Hwa Young's biological son?

146
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:24,740
You can't blame him for that!

147
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:26,710
Shut up.

148
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,450
Don't you dare say another word.
Just be quiet.

149
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:33,450
If you hadn't cheated on me
with Chae Hwa Young,

150
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:36,490
it wouldn't matter one bit
if Jun Ho was her son or not.

151
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,190
But how could...

152
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:41,460
Jun Ho be the son of the woman
who had an affair with his father?

153
00:08:41,530 --> 00:08:43,730
Why did it have to be Jun Ho? Why?

154
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:46,400
Look, just stop talking
and give me a divorce.

155
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:50,230
If you can't stand seeing Jun Ho and me,
then we'll move out.

156
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,370
That solves everything!

157
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,840
What?

158
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,910
You want to move out...

159
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:57,980
and play happy family
with Chae Hwa Young and Jun Ho?

160
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:01,150
Not a chance.
I'm not giving you a divorce!

161
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,450
After you've torn my heart to shreds,

162
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:07,690
I'll never let you three go on...

163
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:09,290
to live happily ever after.

164
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:13,320
- Mom.
- Then what do you want from me?

165
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:18,560
You want to keep living in a war zone,
crying and fighting every day?

166
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,130
That'd be great for your health, won't it?

167
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:26,600
You're worried about my health?
You, of all people?

168
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:27,710
Don't say it like that.

169
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,380
Do you think I haven't been disappointed
in you too?

170
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:33,710
- What?
- Have you ever...

171
00:09:33,710 --> 00:09:36,350
once put an egg in my ramyeon for me?

172
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:39,150
When I'd ask for an egg in my ramyeon,

173
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,690
you said it was better without it,

174
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:42,650
keeping the broth clean.
You never once did it, right?

175
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,720
You have got to be kidding me.

176
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:50,700
Are you that upset
because I didn't put an egg...

177
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:52,160
in your ramyeon?

178
00:09:52,230 --> 00:09:55,700
It's just an example.
Listing everything would take all day.

179
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,270
So is that why you cheated on me
with Chae Hwa Young?

180
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,140
Because I didn't put an egg
in your ramyeon?

181
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:05,540
Don't make me out to be the only bad guy,
okay?

182
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:09,050
And don't fool yourself into thinking
you're so perfect!

183
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,850
Get out! Get out right now!

184
00:10:17,490 --> 00:10:18,490
I'm not leaving.

185
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:21,090
I can't leave until you sign the papers.
No, I won't leave!

186
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:23,730
Please, just stop.
Aren't you ashamed to act like this?

187
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,030
I'm getting married to Jang Mi soon.

188
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,630
How can you keep fighting like this?

189
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:29,230
And Dad,

190
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:31,800
you're the one who's wrong here.
Apologize to Mom.

191
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:34,240
Try to see it from her perspective.

192
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,090
You wanted to see me?

193
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:52,790
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

194
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:56,390
These are the special instructions
for the VVIP guest arriving this weekend.

195
00:10:57,630 --> 00:11:00,300
This guest? I know them...

196
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:02,370
quite well.

197
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:06,000
Good. Then you'll have no problem
personally taking care of them.

198
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,640
- Personalized service.
- Me?

199
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:12,310
That's a job for the concierge.
It's not my responsibility.

200
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:15,980
So, are you saying you get to choose
your assignments now, Hwa Young?

201
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:20,820
The employee who knows the VVIP best
should be in charge.

202
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:24,820
So, Hwa Young, consider this
a temporary assignment to the concierge.

203
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:28,260
You're really enjoying this power trip,
aren't you?

204
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:30,360
Fine. I'll play your game.

205
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:35,100
This guest gets upset if their water
is even half a degree warmer than eight.

206
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:39,540
As a test, maintain that temperature
without ice...

207
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:40,740
and bring me a glass.

208
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:44,610
But we have a water sommelier for this.
Why should I have to do it?

209
00:11:45,610 --> 00:11:46,840
You certainly have a lot to say.

210
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:50,010
Will you argue and avoid your duties
every time you're given an order?

211
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:53,250
- Should I report this to the Chairman?
- Fine, I get it. I'll do it.

212
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,520
Now go prepare it.

213
00:11:54,890 --> 00:11:58,390
This is a client's request,
so there is no room for error.

214
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,860
I said I get it!

215
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:10,970
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

216
00:12:17,310 --> 00:12:18,310
Chae Hwa Young.

217
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:22,080
- It's over eight degrees.
- It is eight degrees...

218
00:12:22,650 --> 00:12:23,650
exactly.

219
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,500
Chae Hwa Young.

220
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:41,730
You didn't chill the glass beforehand,
did you?

221
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:46,070
Did you not consider that a warm glass
would change the water's temperature?

222
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:49,410
- Do it over.
- What?

223
00:12:49,410 --> 00:12:50,740
I said, do it over.

224
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,590
I chilled the glass,

225
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:07,560
and the water is at the right temperature.

226
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,630
Pour it as you would for the guest.

227
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,070
With two hands.

228
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,020
There are too many bubbles in the water.

229
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,520
You poured it all at once.

230
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:40,160
If there's too much oxygen in the water,
it won't go down smoothly.

231
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:42,230
- Again.
- What now?

232
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:43,760
The water temperature has already changed.

233
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:46,000
Get it to the right temperature,
bring it back, and pour it again.

234
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:48,730
We're going to do this
until you get it right.

235
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,800
Are you serious?

236
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:52,840
What do you think you're playing at?

237
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,510
- This is ridiculous.
- Chae Hwa Young.

238
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:59,540
I'm giving you a hands-on lesson
on how different theory is from practice,

239
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:01,780
and you call this valuable lesson
ridiculous?

240
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:03,580
What on earth did you do
when you were the CEO?

241
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,150
Just date around?

242
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,850
You can't even get something
this simple right.

243
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,790
Why does the CEO need
practical experience?

244
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:13,260
The CEO must know the work firsthand
to manage their staff properly.

245
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:15,760
- You still haven't learned a thing.
- Oh Jang Mi.

246
00:14:16,030 --> 00:14:17,390
I have had just about enough of you!

247
00:14:17,460 --> 00:14:19,800
This is being recorded,
so I'd watch yourself.

248
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:24,570
The Chairman said to record your training
and bring it to him.

249
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:26,570
He what?

250
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:30,640
- This is outrageous.
- This isn't the time to be outraged.

251
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,710
What are you standing around for?
Go on and bring another one.

252
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:46,460
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

253
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,060
Chae Hwa Young.

254
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:57,370
Didn't you wash your hands after lunch?

255
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:01,340
- What?
- The glass smells like food.

256
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:07,380
Our VVIP adheres to a strict
no-fragrance policy.

257
00:15:07,610 --> 00:15:10,350
Everything must be odorless
when you serve the VVIP.

258
00:15:10,980 --> 00:15:12,720
Wash your hands and do it over.

259
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,850
What's the use of an entry-level employee
who can't even do this?

260
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:20,020
As CEO, you only knew theory.
No wonder your on-site work was a mess.

261
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:22,060
Go fix it. Now.

262
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,670
She's giving me the runaround all day
over a single glass of water?

263
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:39,980
If that VVIP isn't this picky
about water... Oh Jang Mi!

264
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,210
You are so dead.

265
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,280
Temperature, my foot.

266
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:55,490
I brought the water.

267
00:15:57,490 --> 00:16:00,930
The VVIP just contacted us to say
they've canceled their appointment.

268
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,530
I have something to get approved,
so if you'll excuse me.

269
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:20,620
Making me jump through hoops all day?

270
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,850
Oh Jang Mi, that wretched witch.

271
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:32,260
Chairman, as you instructed,

272
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:36,430
I've surveyed plastic surgery centers,
both here and abroad.

273
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:39,770
Which place can restore...

274
00:16:40,570 --> 00:16:42,770
Seo Rin's face perfectly?

275
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:46,780
The Regen Global Center in Boston
is unparalleled.

276
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:50,910
They have the most complete recoveries
using stem cell regeneration.

277
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:56,390
- Boston?
- Their data shows a 95 percent or more...

278
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:59,420
chance of regenerating
the original skin tissue.

279
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,720
Excellent.

280
00:17:02,260 --> 00:17:04,030
We have no time to lose.

281
00:17:04,830 --> 00:17:06,200
Find out if the surgery is possible,

282
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,330
how long it will take,

283
00:17:08,870 --> 00:17:10,300
and get me a definitive answer.

284
00:17:10,770 --> 00:17:11,900
Yes, sir.

285
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,340
My dear Seo Rin will be so happy.

286
00:17:20,710 --> 00:17:23,110
- It's me, Ma Seo Rin.
- What is it?

287
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,480
Jun Ho, you heard, didn't you?

288
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:27,150
That Oh Jang Mi and lawyer Kang Baek Ho
are getting married.

289
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:29,250
- "So?"
- What do you mean, "So?"

290
00:17:29,390 --> 00:17:31,160
How can you be so casual about this?

291
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:34,220
Don't you get that we have to get married
before Oh Jang Mi does?

292
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,090
What do you mean, we get married?

293
00:17:36,690 --> 00:17:38,030
Who's marrying whom?

294
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:40,600
Jun Ho, are you really being like this?

295
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:44,770
After everything that's happened,
you're still not over Oh Jang Mi?

296
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:47,870
Shouldn't you be coming to me now?

297
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,470
You...

298
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:52,480
thought you were marrying me,
Ma Seo Rin, didn't you?

299
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:54,850
Don't hide your ambition.

300
00:17:54,980 --> 00:17:56,750
You seem to have the wrong idea.

301
00:17:57,580 --> 00:18:01,850
I knew she was Oh Jang Mi,
and I was going to marry her anyway.

302
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,820
I wasn't trying to marry Ma Seo Rin.

303
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:22,740
Darn it.

304
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:49,670
All right.
If I just leave things like this,

305
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:52,170
Seo Rin will probably just think
she just didn't see them.

306
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,450
(Director Kang Jun Ho)

307
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:08,420
Jang Mi, can we talk for a minute?

308
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:11,820
- About what?
- Is it true that you're marrying Baek Ho?

309
00:19:12,690 --> 00:19:14,160
Who said you could do that?

310
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:17,290
I'm supposed to get your permission?

311
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:21,800
Our wedding was just put on hold.
It wasn't called off.

312
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:25,970
We haven't resolved anything,
and you're just marrying another man?

313
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,400
Why are you acting like this,
General Manager Kang?

314
00:19:28,010 --> 00:19:30,110
I've made it clear that I love Baek Ho,

315
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:33,140
and our marriage was for business,
not love.

316
00:19:33,710 --> 00:19:36,550
You know this perfectly well,
so why are you acting like this now?

317
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:41,490
I never thought of it as just business.

318
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:43,320
My feelings for you...

319
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,420
were real.

320
00:19:45,690 --> 00:19:46,790
Please, don't do this.

321
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,230
I'm going to marry Baek Ho.

322
00:19:49,830 --> 00:19:51,430
So the next time we meet,
you'll be my brother-in-law.

323
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:57,970
Oh, Jang Mi,
how far are you planning to push me?

324
00:19:58,170 --> 00:20:01,840
If I'm laying my heart out like this,
shouldn't you back down and accept me?

325
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:04,110
Let go of me! We're at work.

326
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:05,810
Is it because I'm Chae Hwa Young's son?

327
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:08,580
- Is that it?
- You know the answer, so why ask?

328
00:20:09,210 --> 00:20:10,510
Now, please let me go.

329
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:13,520
Any more than this is just obsession.

330
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,950
- Just like Chae Hwa Young.
- Oh Jang Mi!

331
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,490
Get your hands off her!

332
00:20:21,390 --> 00:20:23,430
- Jang Mi, are you okay?
- I'm fine.

333
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,560
Jun Ho, I'm warning you.

334
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,100
If you so much as lay a finger
on my woman again,

335
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:30,000
I don't know what I'm capable of.

336
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:32,100
- Mark my words.
- Kang Baek Ho.

337
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,440
You're the one who needs to back off.
Understand?

338
00:20:35,710 --> 00:20:37,640
Stop it. We're at work.

339
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:39,710
Baek Ho, let's go.

340
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:45,580
Darn it.

341
00:20:48,990 --> 00:20:50,220
No, Jang Mi.

342
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:53,120
I will never...

343
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:56,160
be the one who gets abandoned.

344
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,360
The one who gets abandoned
will be Baek Ho.

345
00:21:01,930 --> 00:21:02,930
Just you watch.

346
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,210
Are you okay?

347
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:13,880
Why did you have to get physical?
What if you'd gotten hurt?

348
00:21:13,940 --> 00:21:16,880
What man would just stand by and watch
while his girl is being harassed?

349
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:22,220
What do you take me for?
Did it look like I couldn't handle myself?

350
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:24,960
I guess you have a point.

351
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:27,690
Anyway, my Jang Mi is...

352
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,330
- Your Jang Mi is what?
- Adorable.

353
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:32,930
Come on.

354
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:36,800
Jang Mi, I've been thinking...

355
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:40,000
How about we have
a commitment ceremony first?

356
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:41,370
A commitment ceremony?

357
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:45,140
A big wedding with friends and family
will be great,

358
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,240
but it'll be so hectic.

359
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:51,950
Let's share a moment just for us
and have a small, private wedding first.

360
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:54,350
A small, private wedding beforehand?

361
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:58,090
Baek Ho, you're really in a hurry.

362
00:21:58,390 --> 00:21:59,590
Well, you know...

363
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:01,760
I am.

364
00:22:02,590 --> 00:22:04,900
I've already planned the honeymoon, too.

365
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,760
What? The honeymoon?

366
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,800
Wait,
you're going on your honeymoon first?

367
00:22:10,730 --> 00:22:12,100
Baek Ho, is that true?

368
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,170
Yes, it's true.

369
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:37,730
Lee Kang Hyuk.

370
00:22:38,530 --> 00:22:42,870
So this is why you've been
Chae Hwa Young's lapdog?

371
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:48,710
Chae Hwa Young, Kang Nam Bong.

372
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,480
I won't let you two get away with this.

373
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:55,050
They've messed with the wrong person.

374
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:04,050
Yes.
Are you still looking into Manager Lee?

375
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:07,090
He apparently was in the same orphanage
as Chae Hwa Young.

376
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:10,860
- Since they were kids?
- Yes. And he's never been married.

377
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:14,800
At least he has some conscience.

378
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:19,140
He didn't make some poor woman miserable
while he was pining for CEO Chae.

379
00:23:19,270 --> 00:23:20,370
He's hopelessly devoted.

380
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,440
Which means...

381
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:25,380
watching Chae Hwa Young
fool around with Kang Nam Bong...

382
00:23:25,710 --> 00:23:27,510
must be eating him up inside.

383
00:23:29,110 --> 00:23:30,180
What are you talking about?

384
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:34,650
Chairman Ma had a daughter,
and you think she is Jung Suk Hee?

385
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:37,950
No, that can't be right. It's impossible.

386
00:23:39,190 --> 00:23:42,090
- But I have a bad feeling about this.
- It doesn't make any sense.

387
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,030
Then Ma Dong Seok
didn't know she was his own sister...

388
00:23:45,530 --> 00:23:47,860
- How could a brother and sister?
- It's not certain yet.

389
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,970
Whether she's his older or younger sister.

390
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:52,370
How old did they say Suk Hee was again?

391
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:55,410
As far as I know,
she's younger than Ma Dong Seok.

392
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:57,210
But that's strange.

393
00:23:57,910 --> 00:23:59,880
If Dong Seok was born first,

394
00:24:00,340 --> 00:24:02,810
then why isn't he
in any of the family photos?

395
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:06,980
And she can't be the older sister.
Their ages don't line up.

396
00:24:07,820 --> 00:24:10,050
- Then it can't be her.
- But what if...

397
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:11,890
What if by some one-in-a-million chance,

398
00:24:12,590 --> 00:24:14,320
Jung Suk Hee really is
the Chairman's daughter...

399
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:17,590
I can't even bear to think about it.

400
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:20,830
Stop with the wild imagination.
Does that really make any sense to you?

401
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,970
Twins born to a brother and sister?

402
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:25,970
That can't be it.

403
00:24:26,970 --> 00:24:28,570
Still, something keeps bothering me.

404
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:31,070
Why do they both have
the same four-leaf clover?

405
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:33,910
Chairman.

406
00:24:34,210 --> 00:24:37,610
You have a visitor from LA to see you.

407
00:24:38,850 --> 00:24:39,850
Seong Hye...

408
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:43,050
Is it really you, Seong Hye?

409
00:24:43,450 --> 00:24:44,590
It's been a long time.

410
00:24:45,660 --> 00:24:47,660
So much time has passed, hasn't it?

411
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:52,930
You're as lovely as ever.

412
00:24:52,930 --> 00:24:54,830
It's like time has stood still for you.

413
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,830
I'd recognize you anywhere.

414
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:58,970
You're too kind.

415
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,200
What is this?

416
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,870
Will you look at them,
so happy to see each other.

417
00:25:03,010 --> 00:25:05,310
How long has it been
for this emotional reunion?

418
00:25:05,510 --> 00:25:08,450
So, when did you arrive in Korea?

419
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:09,850
I got in yesterday.

420
00:25:10,510 --> 00:25:12,520
I was going to call you, Chairman, but...

421
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:16,890
You should have!
I'd have dropped everything and run over.

422
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:19,320
Anyway, it's so good to see you.

423
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:22,260
Honey.

424
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:25,700
We have a guest.
What kind of tea should I serve?

425
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:29,030
Geum Soon, you need to bring some tea.

426
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:31,700
That's all right. We can have tea later.

427
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:34,570
Did you get remarried?

428
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,310
Remarried? Of course not.

429
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:38,040
She's just a housekeeper.

430
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,310
Pay her no mind.

431
00:25:39,310 --> 00:25:40,680
Now, let's go inside.

432
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:45,180
Goodness... Honey!

433
00:25:54,290 --> 00:25:57,460
Are you laughing?
What do you find so funny, Geum Soon?

434
00:25:57,660 --> 00:25:59,630
Do you want to make a scene
in front of our guest?

435
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:02,370
Looks like we're in the same boat,
you and I.

436
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:08,940
I'm so furious.

437
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:13,540
You must still hate me so much.

438
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:17,450
What made you decide to visit?

439
00:26:18,180 --> 00:26:19,520
I'm too old for that now.

440
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:25,420
After all the hardships
I went through in America,

441
00:26:27,890 --> 00:26:31,760
what was the point of holding grudges
at my age?

442
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:33,830
That's what I came to realize.

443
00:26:34,430 --> 00:26:36,730
So I decided...

444
00:26:36,730 --> 00:26:40,170
I wanted to see you
and clear the air before I die.

445
00:26:40,340 --> 00:26:43,070
I'm grateful you feel that way.

446
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:47,610
When I think about it,
I completely understand.

447
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:50,250
It's my fault
your only sister and your niece...

448
00:26:51,180 --> 00:26:52,880
are gone.

449
00:26:54,150 --> 00:26:56,820
I can only imagine how much
you must have wanted to kill me.

450
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,590
There's nothing I can say for myself.

451
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:01,960
Listen.

452
00:27:02,430 --> 00:27:06,860
I came all this way because I have
something important to tell you.

453
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,400
What is it?

454
00:27:08,730 --> 00:27:12,000
Our Eun Hye isn't dead.

455
00:27:12,970 --> 00:27:13,970
What...

456
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:16,470
What did you just say?

457
00:27:16,770 --> 00:27:17,910
Our Eun Hye,

458
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:21,240
your daughter, who you've believed
was dead all this time,

459
00:27:22,180 --> 00:27:24,110
is alive.

460
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:25,920
What?

461
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:30,220
My Eun Hye is alive?

462
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:43,200
I'm not going to lose it this time.

463
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,240
I'll make sure Grandfather
gets his present.

464
00:28:09,690 --> 00:28:11,330
(The First Man)

465
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:14,430
Are you hurt?

466
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:16,130
Oh no. I've spilled it all over you.

467
00:28:16,870 --> 00:28:18,640
- Take it off.
- Excuse me?

468
00:28:18,940 --> 00:28:20,700
Why would Dad leave this necklace here?

469
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,810
But where's its match?
This looks like it's only half of a set.

470
00:28:23,940 --> 00:28:26,010
This is mine! It's Suk Hee's!

471
00:28:26,210 --> 00:28:29,450
Jang Mi, you're like a shining light.

472
00:28:29,710 --> 00:28:30,780
I realize now...

473
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:34,280
that a life with you, Baek Ho,
will be beautiful.

474
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:40,290
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
